## Comments in JavaScript

Comments in JavaScript are used to explain code and make programs easier to understand. Comments are ignored by
the JavaScript interpreter and do not affect program execution. They help programmers document their code and 
improve readability. Comments are useful when working on large projects because they make it easier for 
developers to understand program logic. They are also used for debugging by temporarily disabling parts of code. 
Good comments improve maintenance and collaboration among team members.

### Types of Comments in JavaScript:

### 1. Single-line Comment

Single-line comments are used to write comments on one line. They begin with `//`.

**Example:**

```javascript
// This is a single-line comment

let age = 20;
console.log(age);
```

---

### 2. Multi-line Comment

Multi-line comments are used for comments that span multiple lines. They begin with `/*` and end with `*/`.

**Example:**

```javascript
/*
This is a multi-line comment.
It can cover multiple lines.
*/

let name = "John";
console.log(name);
```

### Advantages of Comments:

* Improves code readability
* Helps explain program logic
* Makes debugging easier
* Supports teamwork and collaboration
* Simplifies maintenance of programs
